# Spec Kit Project Rule

- When working with `speckit` commands such as `speckit.specify`, `speckit.constitution`, `speckit.clarify`, `speckit.plan`, or `speckit.tasks`, first load and follow the `speckit-project-context` skill.
- Before `speckit.constitution`, `speckit.clarify`, `speckit.specify`, or `speckit.plan`, also load and follow the `specify-prompt-engineer` skill to transform rough user text into a structured command-ready prompt.
- Treat `README.md` and the project files in `docs/` as the current product context.
- If `docs/`, the constitution, and generated spec artifacts disagree, surface the conflict and resolve it explicitly before proceeding.
- For frontend or `Next.js` planning, also consider `.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices` and `.agents/skills/vercel-composition-patterns`.
- For AI UI or AI product flows, also consider `.agents/skills/ai-elements` and `.agents/skills/ai-sdk`.

